Dai-Ichi $1.3 Billion of Perpetual Bonds Drop, Trace Data Show

-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 
2011-03-14T12:37:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/dai-ichi-1-3-billion-of-perpetual-bonds-drop-trace-data-show.html
Bonds of the Dai-Ichi Life
Insurance Co.,  Japan ’s second-biggest life insurer, declined in
trading less than a week after issuance.  It’s $1.3 billion of 7.25 percent perpetual bonds fell 1.7
cents to 98.9 cents on the dollar, according to Trace, the bond
price reporting system of the Financial Industry Regulatory
Authority. The Tokyo-based insurer issued the notes on March 8,
three days before a temblor and an ensuing tsunami struck Japan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Pierre Paulden at 
 ppaulden@bloomberg.net  